    <!-- Harmonies -->
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.WindowTitle">Color harmonies — TMHue</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Title">Color harmonies</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Subtitle">Suggestions from a base color</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip1a">Picked a color and don't know what goes with it?</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip1b"> That's exactly what this tool solves: enter a color and TMHue suggests ready-made palettes that work together.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip2a">How to use:</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip2b"> type the color in the field below or click the colored square to pick it from anywhere on screen with the eyedropper.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip3a">Each section is a combination style — hover the </sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip3b">?</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip3c"> on each one to understand when to use it. Click any color to copy it.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tip4">Ideal for building the visual identity of a site, presentation or design without relying on eyeballing.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.BaseColor">Base color</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.PickBaseTip">Pick the base color with the eyedropper (with mini zoom)</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Complementary">Complementary</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.ComplementaryDesc">The opposite color on the color wheel (180° away). Creates the strongest possible contrast — ideal for highlighting buttons and calls to action.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Analogous">Analogous</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.AnalogousDesc">Neighboring colors on the color wheel (30° to each side). They combine naturally and create soft, harmonious visuals.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Triadic">Triadic</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.TriadicDesc">Three colors evenly spaced on the color wheel (120° apart). Balances contrast and harmony — vibrant palettes without losing cohesion.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tetradic">Tetradic</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.TetradicDesc">Four colors evenly spaced on the color wheel (90° apart). Offers more variety; works best when one color dominates and the others accent.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Tints">Tints</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.TintsDesc">The same color progressively lighter, toward white. Useful for backgrounds, hover states and visual hierarchy.</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.Shades">Shades</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="L.Harmony.ShadesDesc">The same color progressively darker, toward black. Useful for text, borders and pressed states.</sys:String>

